description: This one had been buried, which is fairly obvious from the sand on the scat itself. Pic 2 shows my excavation of the scat with the cat’s scrapings to its right (only just visible because rather shallow). (Never easy to see things like this in sand on a photo – one reason I try to avoid IDing spoor!) Caracal sometimes bury their droppings and sometimes don’t. The soft sand in the stream bed probably made it easy for the cat. There was a caracal sighting in the vicinity recently (no pics though).
